2026-07-14 FOUNDATION: taxonomy + 30 seed companies + chokepoint hypotheses + sources.
2026-07-16 FIX: chokepoint column normalized from TRUE/FALSE to yes/no. Not cosmetic. The artifact template tests c.chokepoint==='yes', so every chokepoint in this map would have rendered as NOT a chokepoint the moment the map was built, showing "0 chokepoints flagged" with no error raised. Six of the nine foundations had this drift (different research agents wrote different vocabularies); the four others were already yes/no. Counts preserved exactly. Now enforced by tools/gate.sh.

2026-07-17 RENDERS NOW: added map.json (12 value-chain layers, 6 chokepoint_why lines) so shared/build_map.py can draw this map. Built artifact/ai-compute-map.html: 30 companies land in a layer, zero orphans, every chokepoint carries an explanation. Authored mechanically from FOUNDATION.md + companies.csv (a Haiku worker); the layer roles were extracted from companies.csv, not invented, and the build's orphan + chokepoint_why checks were the gate. STILL foundation only: 0 costed companies, 0 sourced relationship edges. NEXT is a financials or relationships burst.

2026-07-20 FINANCIALS (part 1), BY REUSE NOT BY RESEARCH: 12 of 30 companies costed at tier 1 without a
single fetch. 04's own FOUNDATION.md always said its overlap with 01-semiconductor was deliberate --
"literally the same company viewed through a different lens" -- and 01 had already costed twelve of these
from primary filings, including FIVE OF THE SIX CHOKEPOINTS (Nvidia, TSMC, SK hynix, Samsung, Micron).
The atlas had been treating that as a coincidence instead of an asset.

New tools/reuse_costed.py does the copy, because retyping is where wrong numbers come from. It carries the
provenance (fiscal_year, filing_source, source_tier, last_updated) AND the source row's figure caveats
verbatim -- TSMC's filed NT$31.11 rate, Samsung's attributable-to-parent line, Intel's capex being gross
additions -- so a qualified number does not arrive bare. It refuses to overwrite any non-empty cell.

WHY IT HAS NO FUZZY MATCHING. While planning this, a throwaway substring matcher run over the real CSVs
matched Samsung SDI -> Samsung Electronics and would have written Samsung's $234.62B onto SDI's row. Two
different listed companies; that is check_identity.py's NEO -> NEOGENOMICS failure in a new costume. So
identity is exact-string or an approved row in the new shared/company_aliases.csv, nothing else. The
selftest carries that exact pair as its sharpest NEGATIVE, and six mutants were run against it -- one of
which "went red" by crashing rather than asserting, which is its own kind of broken control, now fixed.

STILL foundation-adjacent, not Mapped: 0 relationship edges, and Siemens Energy (the sixth chokepoint) is
not costed. NEXT: the SEC-filer batch (Marvell, Arista, Astera Labs, Super Micro, Dell, HPE, Vertiv, Eaton,
Oracle, CoreWeave, Nebius via tools/xbrl_extract.py), then Siemens Energy on a new Xetra route, then the
relationships burst. Cerebras, Groq, OpenAI and Anthropic stay blank on purpose: private, no audited filing.

2026-07-20 FINANCIALS (part 2), THE SEC BATCH: 11 more companies costed at tier 1, taking 04 to 23 of 30.
Marvell, Arista, Astera Labs, Super Micro, Dell, HPE, Vertiv, Eaton, Oracle, CoreWeave and Nebius, all
through tools/xbrl_extract.py against SEC XBRL companyfacts. Routed first, per shared/SOURCING-ROUTES.md:
ONE fetch of company_tickers.json resolved all eleven and printed all eleven registrants for approval,
rather than eleven separate lookups. Every registrant was read before its binding was approved; the two
worth a second look were ETN (Eaton Corp plc, Ireland domiciled, correct) and NBIS (Nebius Group N.V. on
CIK 1513845, which is the former Yandex N.V. entity renamed, not a collision).

MARKET CAP GOT A BETTER ROUTE THAN 01 HAD. 01 took market caps from trackers (stockanalysis.com,
companiesmarketcap.com) at tier 3 in a tier 1 row. Here the SHARE COUNT comes from the filing cover page
and only the PRICE is market data, so the weaker half is as small as it can be. Before trusting it, the
method was run as a CONTROL against two market caps 01 had already sourced independently: NVDA came out
4940B against 01's 5109B (-3.3%) and MSFT 2990B against 2917B (+2.5%), both consistent with a week of
price drift. That control is what made Oracle's $349B and Super Micro's $14B believable as data rather
than as an instrument error, which is exactly how they first read.

EMPTY WHERE IT SHOULD BE EMPTY. Dell, CoreWeave and Nebius tag no cover-page share count, so their market
cap is blank rather than approximated (Dell's dual class structure would make a single class count wrong
even if one existed). Cerebras, Groq, OpenAI and Anthropic stay blank permanently: private, no audited
filing, and a press reported valuation is not a financial statement.

Two figures that look like typos and are not, both noted in their rows: HPE's FY2025 net income is $0.06B,
down from $2.60B; Oracle's capex is $55.66B against $17.09B of net income. Eaton and Oracle both had a
consolidated ProfitLoss line differing from the attributable one, and the extractor took attributable in
both, which is the rule shared/SOURCING-ROUTES.md states.

NEXT: Siemens Energy (the sixth chokepoint, Xetra, a jurisdiction this repo has no route for yet), then
Schneider Electric and Foxconn, then the relationships burst that would make 04 Mapped.
